## 9. The .gitignore File

`.gitignore` tells Git which files to never track. Place it in the root of your repository.

**What to always ignore:**

```gitignore
# Dependencies
node_modules/
vendor/

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
*.class
*.pyc

# Environment & secrets
.env
.env.local
*.pem

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log
logs/

# IDE files
.idea/
.vscode/
*.suo
```

> **Critical rule:** Never commit secrets, passwords, or API keys. Once pushed to a remote, they are compromised — even if deleted later, the history retains them.

Use [gitignore.io](https://gitignore.io) to generate a `.gitignore` tailored to your language and framework.

