## 11. Git in the CI/CD Pipeline

Version control is the **trigger** for every automated step in a modern software pipeline.

```
Developer
  git push
     ↓
Remote Repo (GitHub/GitLab)
  Webhook fires
     ↓
CI Server (GitHub Actions / Jenkins / GitLab CI)
  ├── Lint & code quality checks
  ├── Unit tests
  ├── Integration tests
  └── Build artefact (Docker image, binary, etc.)
     ↓
CD Pipeline
  ├── Deploy to staging
  └── Deploy to production (on merge to main)
```

**Key principle:** Every commit to `main` should be deployable. This is enforced by automated tests that run on every push and every pull request.

Without version control, there is no event for automation to listen to. Git is the foundation that makes CI/CD possible.

